{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And very little was known in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Even though we were 60 kilometers from Vienna, we did not know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We were kept in the dark.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And there is a serious allegation I must record as far as the Jewish Judenrat committee of Budapest are at fault, or in serious-- under serious accusation that they, for their personal safety-- which I can understand, that everybody tries to look after themselves.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But in that case, they shouldn't take on communal duties.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Then they should resign-- have persistently and actively denied any knowledge of Auschwitz or of any concentration camp for that reason, and kept on reassuring the provincial jury, and for that reason, probably the Budapest jury.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "In other words, actively carrying out the best wishes of Eichmann and the SS that-- not to cause panic, and do everything in an orderly manner.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And if you really think what a fantastic organization it was, that you step into a country, OK, it was an allied country and the Hungarians were more than happy to cooperate.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The Germans didn't need SS troops to carry on the deportations.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They were-- [LAUGHS] just because recently we read and hear a lot about Bosnia and Yugoslavia, I want to record it that the Bosnian Muslims had an SS battalion, which is known, who were the people who were guarding the trains to Auschwitz and travelled along it.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The world doesn't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And I know about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And, in fact, I think I've seen an article once in the where that was recorded.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "People think that people are being badly treated for no reason at all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "What the Serbs have suffered is unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Tito was a Croat, as it happened, but he was a Communist.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And this is maybe politicizing, but it has to do with Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
